## 7. Event-Driven Feedback (not timer polling)

Prefer attaching `EventHandler` to component status controls over timer-based polling:

```lua
-- ✅ Event-driven — fires only when state actually changes
if comp["ledSystemPower"] then
    comp["ledSystemPower"].EventHandler = function(ctl)
        debugPrint("System power → " .. (ctl.Boolean and "ON" or "OFF") .. " (Source: Room Controls)")
        updatePowerFeedback()
    end
    debugPrint("Registered: system power handler")
end

-- ❌ Timer polling — runs on a schedule regardless of change
local timer = Timer.New()
timer.EventHandler = function() updatePowerFeedback() end
timer:Start(1.0)
```

Use a timer **only** when hardware cannot notify on change (true polling requirement with no available status control).

---

## 8. Start / Factory Pattern

```lua
local ok, err = pcall(function()
    print("Initializing controller for " .. roomName .. "...")
    if not validateControls() then error("Control validation failed") end
    normalizeControlArrays()
    init()
end)

if ok then
    print("✓ Controller initialized for " .. roomName)
else
    print("✗ ERROR: Initialization failed: " .. tostring(err))
    if controls and controls.txtStatus then
        setProp(controls.txtStatus, "String", "INIT FAILED")
        setProp(controls.txtStatus, "Value", 2)
    end
end
```

---

## 8.5 UCI showLayer — Avoid Base Layer Toggle

**Anti-pattern (causes EventHandler feedback loops):**
```lua
-- ❌ WRONG — Hiding base layers then immediately showing them toggles Y01-Navbar,
-- which contains nav buttons. That can trigger control EventHandlers and cause
-- btnNavEventHandler to fire repeatedly → infinite loop.
for _, layer in ipairs(layersAll) do
    setLayerVisible(layer, false, "none")  -- includes X01, Y01, Z01
end
showLayers({"X01-ProgramVolume", "Y01-Navbar", "Z01-Base"}, true, "none")
```

**Correct pattern:**
```lua
local layersBase = {"X01-ProgramVolume", "Y01-Navbar", "Z01-Base"}

-- Hide only non-base layers; never hide-then-show base (navbar contains nav buttons)
for _, layer in ipairs(layersAll) do
    if layer ~= "X01-ProgramVolume" and layer ~= "Y01-Navbar" and layer ~= "Z01-Base" then
        setLayerVisible(layer, false, "none")
    end
end
showLayers(layersBase, true, "none")
-- Layers with hideBase=true still call hideBaseLayers() explicitly
```

